6:
Man, it's freezing! Remind me why
we came THIS early in the morning...
9:
Because the forecast said it would
snow.
12:
Snow, huh?\n
The clouds ARE looking a bit
suspicious, now that you mention it.
Let's hurry and—
23:
Ah, a beautiful young maiden, softly
sipping a grande stardrop
snowglobe frappuccino with one
pump of caramel and two pumps of
gingerbread spice...
31:
Hey! Where are you going?! \n
How could you ignore such a
heart-throbbing scene?!
34:
We didn't want to interrupt, uh...\n
What... exactly DID we interrupt?
38:
Glad you asked!\n
Gather round, and listen well!
49:
NEED you ask? Have you not heard
of being "trendy?"\n
Here, read this!
53:
The Oculus? Let's see...\n
"10 Trendy Tricks to be His Holiday
Heart-throb!"
59:
A complete guide to the ancient
Palpebran holiday tradition of
exchanging gifts!
63:
If you follow all the steps to be
trendy, boys have to give you
presents!
66:
I am an ADORABLE girl in an
oversized sweater, drinking a winter
exclusive frappuccino at a cozy
café! The boys will never know what
hit them.
74:
Yup! What do you think of my outfit?
I got Shirano to make it for me.
81:
I'm not familiar with Palpebran
fashion, but I believe there is a fair
likelihood you appear "trendy.
Maybe.
85:
You do? You really do?! \n
Thank you, Stella!
87:
All right! Now I know I am on the
right track, I shall have myself a
boyfriend in no time!
91: EEP! Did I say that out loud?
94:
Well, would you look at the time? It's
been great talking to you, Inaho. Bye!
102:
Now then, back to being trendy!\n
I shall be the most popular girl in all
the land!
Ehehe... Ahahaha!
116:
*sniffle* I did everything the
magazine said, but... but... *hic* No
boyfriend. No presents. Just a huge
headache from all the coffee...
120:
Well, you're welcome to come help
us bake a cake. C'mon, it's about
time you called it a day.
131:
*sigh* NOW what am I to do? I was
looking forward to the
present-swapping ritual.
134:
I dunno, just get yourself a present
and call it done.
137:
Wait, I know! That pretty boy of yours
was saying he—
148:
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT WAS FOR?!\n
You KNOW Soushiro rejected me,
you meanie!
153:
All right, calm down. The holiday's
about giving gifts to people you
love, like family and friends. It
doesn't have to be romantic.
156:
And, if you're good, there's always
Santa. He's this saint who's got a
naughty and nice list, and every
year...
162:
I had no idea. This Santa you speak
of is a genius! He must get
dozens—no, HUNDREDS of presents!
165: I just said he GIVES lots of presents.
168:
Exactly! People swap presents with
people they like, right?
174:
So if he gives presents to as many
people as possible, the ones who
like him will give presents back! I
should have thought of this sooner!
177:
That's a PERFECT plan, Inaho. It can't
POSSIBLY go wrong.
182: But of course! Just you watch, Alk.
185:
I read in the Oculus that the best gift
is something money cannot
buy—your heartfelt smile!\n
Here, Alk, a DAZZLING beam for you!
189:
Wooow. Thanks, Inaho. How
generous of you.
194:
You are very welcome! Now then, we
must make haste! Awa, Mugi, Hie,
call the yokai for a parade! We
march tonight!
207:
Hmm, everything should be ready.
The Terrible Tub-licker cleaned up
an old cart for us, and the tengu let
me borrow a fan to control the wind.
210:
The yokai sleigh is ready for
take-off! All we need is a red-nosed
reindeer!
232:
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?!\n
Go back dow—NOT THAT FAAAAST!
236: Well, it was great knowing them.
239:
So... what are all of you doing in
Starview? You didn't come just to
watch the sleigh take off, did you?
243:
Hah! I'm here on business, sonny.
Those little fox friends of yours asked
me to bring as many copies of the
Yokai Encyclopedia as possible.
245:
All the little tots and tykes get free
copies of the first volume, and I get
my return when they beg their
mummies to buy 'em the next ones.
249:
As for the rest, word got out that
Princess Inaho was giving away gifts.
252:
Goodness knows I've told that silly
girl not to make big promises
without thinking of the
consequences! But does she? No, of
course not.
256:
Reeeally feeling the warm, fuzzy
holiday spirit right now.
259:
I don't know what you expected,
dearie. There's never a quiet day
with Princess Inaho around.
262:
Yes, Starview is always lively when
she's here.
271:
WHEEEEE!\n
This is so FUN! Come on, faster,
faster!
